dct_title_s: Clarke County, Iowa, 1954, aerial photomosaic index
dct_description_sm: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BJX. Form of individual image numbering: BJX-1N-[number], or BJX-2N-[number]."Flying completed 7-8-54" Flown by Puckett Aerial Surveys, Inc. Jackson, Mississippi. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].
